TITLE: Custom Layer-Tap Behavior Definition
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to define a custom layer-tap behavior. It includes the `compatible` property, `#binding-cells`, `flavor`, `tapping-term-ms`, `bindings`, and `display-name` properties. If copied as is, it will overwrite the predefined behavior, so the documentation recommends renaming it. Bindings are specified using momentary-layer and keypress behaviors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk/blob/main/docs/docs/keymaps/behaviors/hold-tap.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dts
CODE:
```
#include <dt-bindings/zmk/behaviors.h>

/ {
    behaviors {
        lt: layer_tap {
            compatible = "zmk,behavior-hold-tap";
            #binding-cells = <2>;
            flavor = "tap-preferred";
            tapping-term-ms = <200>;
            bindings = <&mo>, <&kp>;
            display-name = "Layer-Tap";
        };
    };
};
```

