TITLE: Layer Definition - DTS
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to define a layer within a keymap node, including its bindings. Includes `bindings` property that maps behavior bindings to each key position. `&kp Z` etc. are the key press behaviors bound to respective keys.  Assumes that `#include <behaviors.dtsi>` and `#include <dt-bindings/zmk/keys.h>` have been used.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk/blob/main/docs/docs/keymaps/index.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dts
CODE:
```
keymap {
    compatible = "zmk,keymap";

    default_layer { // Layer 0
        display-name = "Base";
// ----------------------------------------------
// |     Z     |     M     |     K     |
// |     A     |     B     |     C     |
        bindings = <
            &kp Z    &kp M    &kp K
            &kp A    &kp B    &kp C
        >;
    };
};
```

