TITLE: pinctrl Configuration for I2C in DTS - DTS
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `pinctrl` configuration for the I2C bus.  The `i2c0_default` and `i2c0_sleep` configurations specify the pin assignments and power settings for the I2C bus in different modes.  This configuration uses `NRF_PSEL` to define the pins, allowing for flexibility in pin configuration and power management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk/blob/main/docs/blog/2023-04-06-zephyr-3-2.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: dts
CODE:
```
&pinctrl {
       i2c0_default: i2c0_default {
               group1 {
                       psels = <NRF_PSEL(TWIM_SDA, 0, 17)>,
                               <NRF_PSEL(TWIM_SCL, 0, 20)>;
               };
       };

       i2c0_sleep: i2c0_sleep {
               group1 {
                       psels = <NRF_PSEL(TWIM_SDA, 0, 17)>,
                               <NRF_PSEL(TWIM_SCL, 0, 20)>;
                       low-power-enable;
               };
       };
};
```

