TITLE: Home-Row Mod Left Behavior Definition
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to define a custom home-row mod left behavior. It uses the "balanced" flavor and defines properties like `require-prior-idle-ms`, `tapping-term-ms`, `quick-tap-ms`, `bindings`, `hold-trigger-key-positions`, and `hold-trigger-on-release`. This snippet requires the `zmk,behavior-hold-tap` compatible property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk/blob/main/docs/docs/keymaps/behaviors/hold-tap.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: dts
CODE:
```
/ {
    behaviors {
        hml: home_row_mod_left {
            compatible = "zmk,behavior-hold-tap";
            #binding-cells = <2>;
            flavor = "balanced";
            require-prior-idle-ms = <150>;
            tapping-term-ms = <280>;
            quick-tap-ms = <175>;
            bindings = <&kp>, <&kp>;
            hold-trigger-key-positions = < ... >; // List of keys on the right side of the keyboard
            hold-trigger-on-release;
        };
        hmr: home_row_mod_right {
            compatible = "zmk,behavior-hold-tap";
            compatible = "zmk,behavior-hold-tap";
            #binding-cells = <2>;
            flavor = "balanced";
            require-prior-idle-ms = <150>;
            tapping-term-ms = <280>;
            quick-tap-ms = <175>;
            bindings = <&kp>, <&kp>;
            hold-trigger-key-positions = < ... >; // List of keys on the left side of the keyboard
            hold-trigger-on-release;
        };
    };
};
```

