TITLE: Configuring UART0 Pins for RP2040
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures the pins for UART0 on the RP2040. It utilizes the rpi-pico-rp2040-pinctrl.h header for pin definitions and sets P0 as UART0 TX and P1 as UART0 RX, enabling input on P1.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk/blob/main/docs/docs/development/hardware-integration/pinctrl.mdx#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: dts
CODE:
```
&pinctrl {
    /* configuration for the usart0 "default" state */
    uart0_default: uart0_default {
        group1 {
            /* configure P0 as UART0 TX */
            pinmux = <UART0_TX_P0>;
            };
        group2 {
            /* configure P1 as UART0 RX */
            pinmux = <UART0_RX_P1>;
            /* enable input on pin 1 */
            input-enable;
        };
    };
};
```

